==Production==

===Development===
In August 2013, reports announced that [[Dhanush]] would play the lead role in [[R. Balki]]'s next film.<ref>Iyer, Meena (21 August 2013). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/ready-for-R-Balki/articleshow/21934923.cms "ready for R Balki?"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> But Balki denied them as rumors, citing that they may have arisen when he had shot for an advertisement featuring.<ref>[[Subhash K. Jha|K. Jha, Subhash]] (6 March 2013). [http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-no-shah-rukh-khan-only-amitabh-bachchan-in-r-balkis-next-1807860 "No Shah Rukh Khan, only Amitabh Bachchan in R. Balki's next"]. ''[[Daily News and Analysis|Daily News and Analaysis, India Edition]]''. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> In November 2013, [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and Dhanush were announced as feature in the lead roles. The film also marked the acting debut of [[Kamal Haasan]]'s second daughter, [[Akshara Haasan]].<ref name=BOI>[http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/big-b-dhanush-akshara-haasan-in-r-balki%E2%80%99s-next/ "Big B-Dhanush-Akshara Haasan In R Balki’s Next"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821024351/http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/big-b-dhanush-akshara-haasan-in-r-balki%E2%80%99s-next/ |date=21 August 2014 }}. ''[[Box Office India]]''. 16 November 2013. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> In addition to portraying one of the film's central characters, Amitabh Bachchan had also bankrolled the venture.<ref>Baksi, Dibyojyoti (9 April 2014). [http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-to-co-produce-r-balki-s-next/article1-1205990.aspx "Amitabh Bachchan to co-produce R Balki's next"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821095811/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-to-co-produce-r-balki-s-next/article1-1205990.aspx |date=21 August 2014 }}. ''[[Hindustan Times]]''. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> In May 2014, Balki revealed that the film would be titled ''Shamitabh'', which also sounded similar to the [[Bollywood]] star's name,<ref>[http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/r-balki-s-next-titled-shamitabh_155776.html "R. Balki's next titled 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[Zee News]]''. 30 May 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> whilst also revealing that half the film's shooting had been completed.<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/r-balki-s-next-titled-shamitabh-news-bollywood-of3saWjdghgsi.html "R. Balki's next titled 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[Sify]]''. 30 May 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> Amitabh Bachchan lent his voice to Dhanush, who plays a dumb aspiring actor in the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/amitabh-bachchan-to-give-voice-over-to-dhanush/|title=Amitabh Bachchan to give voice-over to Dhanush|work=[[The Indian Express]]}} 18 July 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> The film's title derived from the duo's names in which 'Sh' from Dhanush was added as a prefix to Amitabh, therefore becoming ''Shamitabh''.<ref>[http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-popular/amitabh-bachchans-next-with-r-balki-is-titled-shamitabh/ "Amitabh Bachchan’s Next With R Balki Is Titled 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[Koimoi]]''. 30 May 2014. Retrieved 21 August 2014.</ref>

===Casting===
Besides the lead cast,<ref name = BOI/> it was confirmed in February 2014 that actor Rajeev Ravindranathan  would appear in a small role in the film.<ref>Sampath, Parinatha (4 February 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/theatre/Rajeev-Ravindranathan-begins-shoot-for-Balkis-next/movie-review/29849041.cms "Rajeev Ravindranathan begins shoot for R Balki's next"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> Rajeev confirmed the same again in July 2014.<ref>Talukdar, Taniya (23 July 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/theatre/Why-is-Rajeev-Ravindranathan-tight-lipped-about-his-next-film/articleshow/38861953.cms "Why is Rajeev Ravindranathan tight-lipped about his next film?"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> In August 2014, it was reported that director [[Mahesh Bhatt]] had acted in a cameo role in the film.<ref>[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7035 "Check out: Mahesh Bhatt does a cameo in 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[Bollywood Hungama]]''. 13 August 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref><ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/mahesh-bhatt-acting-r-balki-shamitabh-dhanush/1/376935.html "Mahesh Bhatt turns actor for R Balki's 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[India Today]]''. 13 August 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> Later it was reported that not only Mahesh Bhatt, but [[Karan Johar]], [[Anurag Basu]], [[Rakesh Omprakash Mehra]], [[Rajkumar Hirani]], [[Gauri Shinde]], along with lyricist [[Javed Akhtar]] and producers [[Boney Kapoor]] and [[Ekta Kapoor]] would do cameos in the film.<ref>Gupta, Priya (22 August 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Hindi/Bollywood/News/R-Balki-gets-6-directors-to-do-a-cameo-in-Shamitabh/articleshow/40598514.cms "R Balki gets 6 directors to do a cameo in 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 22 August 2014.</ref> Actress [[Abhinaya (actress)|Abhinaya]] of ''[[Nadodigal]]'' (2009) fame was selected to play a crucial role in the film.<ref>Borah, M. Prabalika (1 September 2014). [http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-abhinaya-is-heading-towards-hollywood/article6369872.ece "Going places, quietly"]. ''[[The Hindu]]''. Retrieved 1 October 2014.</ref>  Actress [[Rekha]] was selected to play a supporting role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/one-more-legend-for-dhanush-in-shamitabh.html|title=One more legend for Dhanush|work=[[Behindwoods.com|Behindwoods]]|date=2 October 2014|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref> Vandita Shrivastava, an MBA-turned-actress, stated that she had a role in the film.<ref>{{cite web|author=The author has posted comments on this article |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/The-Shaukeens-actress-Vandita-to-be-seen-in-Shamitabh/articleshow/45468155.cms |title=The Shaukeens actress Vandita to be seen in Shamitabh - The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2014-12-11 |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref>

===Filming===
[[Principal photography]] commenced on February 2014 in [[Igatpuri]].<ref name = Shamitabh1 /><ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news-interviews/Dhanush-kick-starts-Balki-film/articleshow/29844872.cms "Dhanush kick starts Balki film!"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 4 February 2014. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> Amitabh Bachchan began shooting for his portions in the film in April 2014.<ref>Dubey, Rachana (22 April 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Big-B-begins-shooting-for-R-Balkis-film/articleshow/34072997.cms "Big B begins shooting for R Balki's film"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 20 August 2014.</ref> ''Shamitabh'' became the first Bollywood film to be shot in the [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]] region of Finland and in [[Helsinki]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Jha, Sumit|title='Shamitabh' will be the Bollywood's first movie to be shot in Finland|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Shamitabh-will-be-the-Bollywoods-first-movie-to-be-shot-in-Finland/articleshow/37121709.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]}} 24 June 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=[[Subhash K. Jha|K. Jha, Subhash]] |title='Shamitabh' to be shot in Helsinski|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/news/type/view/id/2561301|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]}} 23 June 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> The crew shot some scenes at the Seven Hills Hospital, the same place where Amitabh Bachchan underwent two abdominal surgeries and saw the birth of Aaradhya, his granddaughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/amitabh-bachchans-encounter-with-reality-on-shamitabh-sets/476733-8-66.html|title=Amitabh Bachchan's encounter with reality on 'Shamitabh' sets|work=[[CNN-IBN|IBNLive]]}} 4 June 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> Some scenes were also shot in [[London]].<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Dhanush-shoots-in-London-with-Amitabh-Bachchan/articleshow/37704220.cms? "Dhanush shoots in London with Amitabh Bachchan"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 3 July 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> The team took a break in mid-July 2014 to celebrate Dhanush's birthday and the success of his 25th film, ''[[Velaiyilla Pattathari]]'' (2014).<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Dhanush-celebrates-with-Big-B-and-Akshara-Haasan/articleshow/38787126.cms "Dhanush celebrates with Big B and Akshara Haasan"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 21 July 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> In mid-August 2014, Amitabh Bachchan stated that he had completed his portions for the film,<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/amitabh-bachchan-wraps-up-r.-balkis-shamitabh/1/377784.html "Amitabh Bachchan wraps up R. Balki's 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[India Today]]''. 19 August 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> whilst also confirming that 90% percent of the film's shooting had been completed.<ref>Pathak, Ankur (18 August 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Hindi/Bollywood/News/Amitabh-Bachchans-final-impact/articleshow/40356786.cms "Amitabh Bachchan's final impact"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> Dhanush reportedly did a few dastardly stunts in the film.<ref>[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/dhanush-goes-crazy-for-shamitabh.html "Dhanush goes crazy!"]. ''Behindwoods''. 20 August 2014. Retrieved 21 August 2014.</ref> The film's cinematographer P. C. Sreeram was fascinated by Akshara's acting capability and lack of nervousness while shooting with Dhanush and Amitabh Bachchan and lauded her as a "woman of substance".<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Akshara-Haasan-a-woman-of-substance/articleshow/40258743.cms?intenttarget=no "Akshara Haasan a woman of substance"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 14 August 2014. Retrieved 19 August 2014.</ref> Akshara did her own choreography for her dance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/more/news/view/id/2647437|title=Akshara Haasan turns choreographer for 'Shamitabh'|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|author=[[Subhash K. Jha|K. Jha, Subhash]]|date=16 September 2014|accessdate=16 September 2014}}</ref>

During the shooting of the film in Finland, a [[Winter storm|snow storm]] hit the area where shooting was going on for a dance sequence in the film and had to immediately walk back towards a safer environment. Hence, they walked for about 10 kilometers with their heavy equipment. Choreographers Bosco-Caesar decided to continue with it and shot the song the next day since a delay would have caused permission trouble.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchans-shamitabh-cast-and-crew-face-storm-trouble-in-finland/|title=Amitabh Bachchan's 'Shamitabh' cast and crew face storm trouble in Finland|work=[[The Indian Express]]}} 1 July 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref><!-- http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/short-takes-column-shamitabh/article6912932.ece -->

