==Promotion and release==
The film released worldwide on 6 February 2015.{{Update after|2015|02|07}}<ref name = OIS/><ref name =IBTimesS/><ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Dhanush-reveals-Shamitabh-plans/articleshow/40387592.cms "Dhanush reveals 'Shamitabh' plans"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 19 August 2014. Retrieved 27 August 2014.</ref>

The first look of the lead actors Amitabh Bachchan and Dhanush were released on 23 July 2014,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/photos/entertainment/from-bhai-to-bhau-salman-speaks-marathi-17776/slide/9|title=Revealed: Amitabh Bachchan's New Look in R Balki's |work=[[NDTV]]|date=22 July 2014|accessdate=7 August 2014|author=Nagwekar, Santosh}}</ref> and 25 July 2014,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://freepressjournal.in/first-look-big-b-dhanush-in-shamitabh/|title=First Look: Big B & Dhanush in 'Shamitabh'|work=[[The Free Press Journal]]}} 25 July 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> respectively. A video trailer of Amitabh sitting in a toilet and singing "piddly si baatein", a catchy, peppy song while holding the script, was released on 31 December 2014. An extended version of the trailer was released on 2 January 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://dehubs.com/upcoming/amitabh-bachchan-rekha-meet-again-watch-shamitabh-trailer/|title = Amitabh Bachchan & Rekha Meet Again - Watch Shamitabh ExtendedTrailer|date = |work = |access-date = }}</ref> Amitabh Bachchan had been reportedly seen sporting a rugged look and wearing shabby clothes,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/snapshot-a-disheveled-amitabh-bachchan-is-spotted-wearing-shabby-clothes-on-the-sets-of-shamitabh/476052-8-66.html|title=Snapshot: A disheveled Amitabh Bachchan is spotted wearing shabby clothes on the sets of 'Shamitabh'|work=[[CNN-IBN|IBNLive]]}} 2 June 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> Bachchan found the look quite difficult to preserve throughout the shooting of the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/420912/big-b-shares-039shamitabh039-look.html|title=Big B shares 'Shamitabh' look, says difficult to preserve|work=[[Deccan Herald]]}}  21 July 2014. Retrieved 7 August 2014.</ref> Bachchan described every film he made with Balki as "novel, out of the ordinary and most challenging" and Shamitabh is "no different".<ref>{{cite news|title=Amitabh: 'Shamitabh' is out of the ordinary like all R Balki films |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/bollywood/news/a583377/amitabh-shamitabh-is-out-of-the-ordinary-like-all-r-balki-films.html#~oMe7BmPucbS7uN|author=Joshi, Priya|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=10 July 2014|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref> A still featuring the lead actors was released by Amitabh Bachchan on [[Twitter]] on 20 August 2014.<ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-amitabh-bachchan-reveals-dhanush-and-akshara-s-look-from-shamitabh-2012375 "Amitabh Bachchan reveals Dhanush and Akshara's look from 'Shamitabh'"].The trailer was released on 6 January 2015 ''[[Daily News and Analysis|Daily News and Analaysis, India Edition]]''. 20 August 2014. Retrieved 21 August 2014.</ref> [[Eros International]] distributed the film worldwide.<ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/eros-international-and-r-balki-team-up-for-shamitabh-114082700432_1.html "Eros International and R Balki team up for 'Shamitabh'"]. ''[[Business Standard]]''. 27 August 2014. Retrieved 28 August 2014.</ref>

==Critical reception==
The movie received mixed to positive reviews from critics. Srijana Mitra Das of [[Times of India]] gave it 3.5 stars out of 5 and stated, "Shamitabh has a doubly dramatic act - but less emotion".<ref>{{cite web|author=Share on Twitter |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/Shamitabh/movie-review/46140842.cms |title=Shamitabh Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date= |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref> Indian Express gave the movie 2 stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/shamitabh-movie-review-swings-between-being-intelligent-and-banal/ |title=‘Shamitabh’ movie review: Amitabh Bachchan’s voice powers the movie |publisher=The Indian Express |date=2015-02-09 |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref> Rajeev Masand of IBNLIVe gave the movie 2.5 stars stating "The promising film comes undone by the curse of the second half". The Guardian gave average reviews describing the movie "Amitabh Bachchan in affectionate but incoherent satire".<ref>{{cite web|author=Mike McCahill |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/feb/09/shamitabh-amitabh-bachchan-bollywood-review |title=Shamitabh review – Amitabh Bachchan in affectionate but incoherent satire &#124; Film |publisher=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref>

